cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AI

This paper discusses a trust model for wireless mesh networks, which involves security and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network simulation, which suggests it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of the Dempster-Shafer Theory and dissimilarity test suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves trust aggregation techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
